From: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Date: Fri, 15 Jun 2018 12:27:16 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] ext4: include the illegal physical block in the bad map
 ext4_error msg
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.17.6
Git-commit: bdbd6ce01a70f02e9373a584d0ae9538dcf0a121

commit bdbd6ce01a70f02e9373a584d0ae9538dcf0a121 upstream.

Signed-off-by: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Cc: stable@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/ext4/inode.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/ext4/inode.c b/fs/ext4/inode.c
index c73cb9346aee..b22f1417828f 100644
--- a/fs/ext4/inode.c
+++ b/fs/ext4/inode.c
@@ -402,9 +402,9 @@ static int __check_block_validity(struct inode *inode, const char *func,
 	if (!ext4_data_block_valid(EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb), map->m_pblk,
 				   map->m_len)) {
 		ext4_error_inode(inode, func, line, map->m_pblk,
-				 "lblock %lu mapped to illegal pblock "
+				 "lblock %lu mapped to illegal pblock %llu "
 				 "(length %d)", (unsigned long) map->m_lblk,
-				 map->m_len);
+				 map->m_pblk, map->m_len);
 		return -EFSCORRUPTED;
 	}
 	return 0;
